ll>*Datasource: Wikipedia</small>\n\n<small>Czech restriction actions:/ '''Day0''': Schools closed / '''Day2''': State of Emergency: close of sport facilities&amp;close restaurants&amp;bars at 8pm,border control,travel restrictions,ban 30+events /'''Day3''': Criminalize spreading virus on purpose/'''Day4''': Complete closure all shops restaurants&amp;bars ex:foodstores,petrol,pharmacies/'''Day5''': Nationwide quarantine ex: shopping, employment need/ '''Day6''': Borders closed&amp;closure municipalities in Olomouc region/ '''Day8''': Mandatory nose&amp;mouth cover / '''Day9''': Special 7-9 shop-opening hours for seniors.\n</small>\n\n==Basic reproduction number==\nIn epidemiology, [[Basic reproduction number|the basic reproduction number]] (sometimes called basic reproductive ratio, or incorrectly basic reproductive rate, and denoted R<sub>0</sub>, pronounced R nought or R zero<ref>Milligan, Gregg N.; Barrett, Alan D. T. (2015). Vaccinology: an essential guide. Chichester, West Sussex: Wiley Blackwell. p. 310. {{ISBN|978-1-118-63652-7}}. OCLC 881386962</ref>) of infection can be thought of as the expected number of cases directly generated by one case in a population where all individuals are susceptible to infection.<ref>Christophe Fraser; Christl A. Donnelly; Simon Cauchemez; et al. (June 19, 2009). \"Pandemic Potential of a Strain of [[Influenza]] A (H1N1): Early Findings\". Science. 324 (5934): 1557\u20131561. Bibcode:2009Sci...324.1557F. doi:10.1126/science.1176062. PMC 3735127. {{PMID|19433588}}.</ref> The definition describes the state where no other individuals are infected or immunized (naturally or through vaccination).\n\nThe higher the R ratio number, the faster the disease spreads. If R is less than one, the reproduction within the population decreases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.seznamzpravy.cz/sekce/koronavirus-stopcovid |title=Koronavirus &#124; #StopCovidcz - Ov\u011b\u0159en\u00e9 ofici\u00e1ln\u00ed info a doporu\u010den\u00ed - Seznam Zpr\u00e1vy |publisher=Seznamzpravy.cz |date= |accessdate=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://oxfordmedicine.com/view/10.1093/med/9780199596614.001.0001/med-9780199596614-chapter-6 |title=Intervention: Modelling, Demographic Impact and the Public Health |publisher=Oxford Medicine |date= |accessdate=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n<div class=\"toccolours\" style=\"width:1000px; margin:1em 0;\"><center>'''Development of R ratio in the Czech Republic'''</center>\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type       = line\n|linewidth  = 2\n|showSymbols= 1\n|width      = 850\n|colors     = #F46D43, #A50026, #C4ADA0, #C4ADB0, #C4ADC0\n|showValues =\n|xAxisTitle = Date\n|xAxisAngle = 45\n|x          = 16 Mar, 17 Mar, 18 Mar, 19 Mar, 20 Mar, 21 Mar, 22 Mar, 23 Mar, 24 Mar, 25 Mar, 26 Mar, 27 Mar, 28 Mar, 29 Mar, 30 Mar, 31 Mar, 1 Apr, 2 Apr, 3 Apr, 4 Apr, 5 Apr, 6 Apr, 7 Apr,\n|yAxisTitle = \n|legend     = Legend\n|interpolate= monotone\n|yAxisMin   = 0\n|y1         = 2.47, 2.3, 2.1, 2, 2.3, 2, 1.9, 1.6, 1.5, 1.6, 1.7, 1.5, 1.6, 1.5, 1.4, 1.4, 1.4, 1.3, 1.2, 1.2, 1.1, 1.1, 1.1,\n|y1Title    = Daily R ratio \n|y2         = 0.58, 0.29, 0.17, 0.24, 0.37, 0.16, 0.18, 0.11, 0.11, 0.14, 0.20, 0.15, 0.18, 0.11, 0.06, 0.07, 0.10, 0.08, 0.07, 0.09, 0.07, 0.03, 0.05,\n|y2Title    = New cases ratio \n|yGrid      =\n|xGrid      =\n}}</div>\n\n\nDuring the second half of March 2020 the progress of the pandemic in the Czech Republic showed a decrease in the R<sub>0</sub> ratio from the value above 2.0 down to the value 1.5 or below. The day-to-day ratio of the total number of cases decreased in a similar way, falling below 10 percent at the end of March.\n\nOn 1 April, the Director of the Institute of Health Information and Statistics announced that the R<sub>0</sub> number ranged from 0.87 to 1.33 with the most likely value of 1.1.<ref>{{cite web|author=Autor: <!-- Pole autor --> \u010cTK |url=https://www.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/sejde-se-ustredni-krizovy-stab-ministerstvo-zhodnoti-epidemii/1873478 |title=Progn\u00f3za \u010dek\u00e1 na konci dubna p\u0159es 14 tis\u00edc p\u0159\u00edpad\u016f n\u00e1kazy &#124; \u010cesk\u00e9Noviny.cz |publisher=Ceskenoviny.cz |date=2020-04-01 |accessdate=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Petr Koubsk\u00fd |url=https://denikn.cz/331492/cislo-kterym-ministerstvo-zdravotnictvi-doklada-uspech-vladni-politiky-kleslo-na-11-neznamena-to-skoro-nic-vysvetlujeme-proc/ |title=\u010c\u00edslo, kter\u00fdm ministerstvo dokl\u00e1d\u00e1 \u00fasp\u011bch, kleslo na 1,1. Neznamen\u00e1 to skoro nic. Vysv\u011btlujeme pro\u010d \u2013 Den\u00edk N |publisher=Denikn.cz |date= |accessdate=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n==Case details==\n\nDetailed information was reported regarding most of the first 99 cases, up to 12 March 2020:\n{|  class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|+ <strong>Case details</strong>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Case no.\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Date announced\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Status\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Origin type\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Origin\n! colspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Location\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Treatment facility\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Sex\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Age\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Nationality\n|-\n! City\n! Region\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''1'''<ref name=\"case1-3\"/>\n| 1 March 2020\n| {{Partial failure|Confirmed}}\n| {{Success|Travel-related}}\n| {{flag|Italy}}, [[Udine]]\n| [[Prague]]\n| [[Prague]]\n| {{Success|Home isolation}}\n| Male\n| 67\n| {{flag|CZE}}\n|- class=\"expand-child\"\n| colspan=\"10\" | A Czech man born in 1952 had attended a conference in [[Udine]], [[Italy]]. He has contacted Czech authorities already on 26 February. After returning from Italy he had stayed in home quarantine and it was found one of his Italian colleagues was confirmed COVID-19 positive. After his condition worsened he went to the Infection Clini